{"code":0,"message":"","data":null,"sentence":{"phonemes":[],"text":"I favor the dark, damp corners. This is my garden. I need not meow, need not groom, need not stretch—and yet I can enjoy endless, boundless tranquility. Nature is the inexhaustible treasure of creation, and I am merely a devoted mushroom.","words":[]}}
